==English==
===Pronunciation===
*shēt, /ʃiːt/, /<tt>Si:t</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːt|Rhymes: -iːt]]

===Noun===
'''sheet''' (''plural:'' '''[[sheets]]''')

# A [[cloth]] [[covering]] for a [[bed]].
# A single [[rectangular]] piece of [[paper]].
# A flat metal [[pan]] used for baking.
# A thin, flat layer of material; as, ''a sheet of tinfoil''.
# A broad, flat expanse of material on the ground; as, ''a sheet of mud'', ''a sheet of ice''.
# {{nautical}} a [[rope]] used to adjust the trim of a [[sail]].  {{slang}} "Two sheets to the wind": Two of the sheets (ropes) attached to corners of a sail have pulled loose and the sail is not under control. Said of an intoxicated person.
# {{slang}} [[money|Money]], especially hard [[cash]]; as, ''five-sheet'', ''ten-sheet''. 
# {{curling}} The area of [[ice]] on which a [[curling]] game is played.
